{
  "doc_id": "57053",
  "text": "Davidoff and Dyke were the first to report a case of intracystic haemorrhage of AC associated with a subdural haematoma in 1938 (1). In 2006, Iaconetta et al. published a literature review regarding AC together with an intracystic haemorrhage and subdural haematoma [CITATION_1] . Among over 37 cases, 23 had no history of head trauma. Since then, just two more cases of such a combination have been reported, one in 2008 by Hong et al. and in 2013 by Kahilogullari et al. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ).",
